Events

Educational, challenging, and fun: Those are the goals of each Enneagram Minnesota event, and our Board of Directors works hard to make every annual program a success. Our chapter is committed to presenting a wide spectrum of Enneagram teachers and perspectives. Many events are free or discounted for our members. Learn more about membership here.

Throughout the year, we offer three types of events: workshops, chapter meetings, and discussion groups. We also highlight Minnesota Enneagram member offerings. See more about all of these events below.

As we are based in Minnesota, all events occur in Central Time.



WORKSHOPS

As highlights of each program year, we offer innovative workshops featuring nationally and internationally known Enneagram teachers. These workshops are typically one to two-and-a-half days in length, offered once or twice a year, and require advance registration and payment. Members receive a discount on registration fees.


CHAPTER meetings

Minnesota Enneagram is fortunate to have excellent Enneagram teachers and presenters living right here in our local community, and with our online meetings we have presenters from all over. These events are free for members, people 30 and under, and first-time guests.


DISCUSSION GROUPS

Our informal Discussion Groups, now online, have become crucial to keeping us connected during the pandemic. The groups are open to the public, free of charge, and moderated by a knowledgeable Enneagram Minnesota Board Member. Discussion Groups are a great way to introduce friends and relatives to the Enneagram.

Enneagram Practitioners LUnch Hour Discussion Group

3rd Tuesday of the month
12:00-1:00pm CT on Zoom
2023 programming year dates:  Jan 17, Feb 21, March 21, April 18, May 16.

Each month we focus on a different topic to launch the discussion, while also leaving space for questions participants are bringing to the group. Free and open to all who self-identify as Enneagram practitioners. Participants need not reside in Minnesota.

Enneagram Minnesota MEMBER OFFERINGS

Enneagram Minnesota provides information on upcoming Enneagram-related classes or presentations, offered by local teachers who are members of our chapter. These events are not sponsored by Enneagram Minnesota, and any questions must be directed to the teacher.
